<DoxygenPage pluginConfig={pluginConfig}>

## Description {#details}

This file provides the implementation of the <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/passbuilder">PassBuilder</a> based on our static pass registry as well as related functionality.

It also provides helpers to aid in analyzing, debugging, and testing passes and pass pipelines.

<SectionDefinition>

## Functions

### callbacksAcceptPassName() {#a39083de9ca15e7350b75526552814775}

<MemberDefinition
  template={<>template &lt;typename PassManagerT, typename CallbacksT&gt;</>}
  prototype={<>static bool callbacksAcceptPassName (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/stringref">StringRef</a> Name, CallbacksT &amp; Callbacks)</>}
  labels = {["static"]}>
Tests whether registered callbacks will accept a given pass name.

When parsing a pipeline text, the type of the outermost pipeline may be omitted, in which case the type is automatically determined from the first pass name in the text. This may be a name that is handled through one of the callbacks. We check this through the oridinary parsing callbacks by setting up a dummy <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/passmanager">PassManager</a> in order to not force the client to also handle this type of query.

Definition at line <a href="#l01424">1424</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/passes/passbuilder-cpp">PassBuilder.cpp</a>.
</MemberDefinition>
